            <bioghist>
                <p>David Jones Reinhardt (1867-1935) was the son of William Dell Reinhardt
                    (1830-1890) and Rebecca Hawley (1841-1915). He was an 1889 graduate of
                    Haverford, and worked as a lawyer and State Senator and Attorney General of
                    Delaware. In 1896 he married Anna Margaret Hewes Reinhardt (1867-1955). Rebecca
                    Hawley Reinhardt's parents were Jesse Hawley (1806-1887) and Esther Meredith
                    Hawley (1807-1900).</p>
            </bioghist>

            <scopecontent>
                <p>This is a collection of papers of the Reinhardt, Hawley and Hewes families.
                    Materials include: correspondence; genealogical materials; photographs; diaries;
                    account books; marriage and baptismal certificates; poetry and Quaker tracts;
                    and obituaries and newspaper clippings. The collection also includes a copy of
                    The Reinhardts and Hawleys of Chester County, PA and the Hewes of Salem County,
                    NJ by Ann McCormack in which many of the letters in this collection have been
                    transcribed.</p>
            </scopecontent>

